promoteToDomainObject

public <T> T promoteToDomainObject(T o)

Can be called multiple times - transforms will be removed after the first

Note - Make sure you change an existing object reference to the returned value if you're going to make further changes to the (now promoted) object - e.g.

mm.wrapper=TransformManager.get().promoteToDomainObject(mm.wrapper); mm.wrapper.setSaved(true);

not

TransformManager.get().promoteToDomainObject(mm.wrapper); mm.wrapper.setSaved(true);

Generally, though, you'll want to do all the modifications on the provisional object so that CollectionModificationListeners on the TransformManager will receive the domain object with all changes applied.

Parameters:
o - - the object to be promoted
Returns:
the newly promoted object, if it implements HasIdAndLocalId, otherwise null
